Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ActionLogicBlock
    An ActionLogicBlock is a LogicBlock that represents an action that should occur in the system when the appropriate triggers have occurred.
    AndLogicBlock
    An AndLogicBlock is a LogicBlock that has an output values of true when the output values of all LogicBlock objects in prevBlocks are true.
    LogicBlock
    A LogicBlock represents one piece of the logical representation of a Service in the system.
    MainController
    The MainController is responsible for connecting all components of the automation framework.
    OrLogicBlock
    An OrLogicBlock is a LogicBlock that has an output value of true when the output value of one or more LogicBlock objects in prevBlocks is true.
    Service
    A Service consists of a set of triggers and actions that are connected with Boolean algebraic statements.
    TriggerLogicBlock
    A TriggerLogicBlock is a LogicBlock that represents a trigger occurring in the system.
    TriggerRequest
    A data structure used for storing trigger requests from peripherals on the request queue.
    WebRequestHandler
    The WebRequestHandler is responsible for handling and parsing requests from the user interface and calling the appropriate methods in the MainController.
